</head>
<body>
    <h1>Shopping Cart Floating Point Demonstration</h1>

    <div class="container">
        <!-- Broken Version (Naive Float Arithmetic) -->
        <div class="cart-section">
            <h2>Broken Cart (Naive Float)</h2>
            <div class="item-input">
                <div>
                    <label for="brokenItemName">Item Name:</label>
                    <input type="text" id="brokenItemName" value="Fancy Gadget">
                </div>
                <div>
                    <label for="brokenItemPrice">Price:</label>
                    <input type="number" id="brokenItemPrice" step="0.01" value="4.99">
                </div>
                <button onclick="addItemToBrokenCart()">Add Item</button>
            </div>

            <h3>Items:</h3>
            <ul id="brokenCartList" class="cart-list">
                <!-- Items will be added here -->
            </ul>
            <div id="brokenCartTotal" class="total">Total: $0.00</div>

            <div class="item-input" style="margin-top: 30px;">
                <div>
                    <label for="brokenCheckPrice">Check if total is:</label>
                    <input type="number" id="brokenCheckPrice" step="0.01" value="14.97">
                </div>
                <button onclick="checkBrokenTotal()">Check Total</button>
            </div>
            <div id="brokenComparisonResult"></div>
        </div>

        <!-- Corrected Version (Integer/String Arithmetic) -->
        <div class="cart-section">
            <h2>Corrected Cart (Proper Decimal Handling)</h2>
            <div class="item-input">
                <div>
                    <label for="correctedItemName">Item Name:</label>
                    <input type="text" id="correctedItemName" value="Mega Widget">
                </div>
                <div>
                    <label for="correctedItemPrice">Price:</label>
                    <input type="number" id="correctedItemPrice" step="0.01" value="4.99">
                </div>
                <button onclick="addItemToCorrectedCart()">Add Item</button>
            </div>

            <h3>Items:</h3>
            <ul id="correctedCartList" class="class-list">
                <!-- Items will be added here -->
            </ul>
            <div id="correctedCartTotal" class="total">Total: $0.00</div>

            <div class="item-input" style="margin-top: 30px;">
                <div>
                    <label for="correctedCheckPrice">Check if total is:</label>
                    <input type="number" id="correctedCheckPrice" step="0.01" value="14.97">
                </div>
                <button onclick="checkCorrectedTotal()">Check Total</button>
            </div>
            <div id="correctedComparisonResult"></div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="explanation">
        <h3>Why Floating-Point Arithmetic Fails for Currency</h3>
        <p>
            Computers store numbers in binary. Decimal fractions (like 0.1, 0.01, 0.99) often cannot be represented
            exactly as finite binary fractions, just like 1/3 cannot be represented exactly as a finite decimal fraction (0.333...).
        </p>
        <p>
            When you perform arithmetic operations (addition, subtraction) with these inexact binary representations,
            small errors accumulate. These errors are often tiny (e.g., <code>0.0000000000000001</code>), but they are
            enough to make a direct comparison using <code>===</code> fail, even if the numbers *should* be equal mathematically.
        </p>
        <p>
            <strong>Example:</strong> In JavaScript, try <code>0.1 + 0.2</code>. You'll get <code>0.30000000000000004</code>, not <code>0.3</code>.
            Similarly, <code>0.1 + 0.1 + 0.1</code> might not be exactly <code>0.3</code>.
        </p>
        <p>
            The developer's claim that <code>===</code> works "perfectly fine" for prices is incorrect because these tiny discrepancies
            will cause comparisons to fail unexpectedly, leading to bugs like incorrect totals, failed price checks,
            or even security vulnerabilities if pricing logic relies on exact float comparisons.
        </p>

        <h3>How the "Broken Cart" Demonstrates This</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>
                It directly uses JavaScript's <code>Number</code> type (floats) for prices and totals.
            </li>
            <li>
                When you add items like $4.99 repeatedly, the internal binary representation accumulates tiny errors.
            </li>
            <li>
                If you add three items of $4.99, the expected total is $14.97. However, the internal float value might be
                something like <code>14.969999999999999</code>.
            </li>
            <li>
                A direct comparison like <code>total === 14.97</code> will then return <code>false</code>, even though visually and mathematically
                it should be true.
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h3>The "Corrected Cart" Solution</h3>
        <p>
            To avoid floating-point issues with currency, you should:
        </p>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <strong>Store prices as integers (cents):</strong> Multiply all prices by 100 (or 1000 for 3 decimal places, etc.)
                and store them as whole numbers. For example, $4.99 becomes 499 cents.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Perform all arithmetic on these integers:</strong> Addition and subtraction on integers are exact.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Convert back to decimal for display:</strong> Only when displaying the value to the user,
                divide by 100 and format it as currency.
            </li>
        </ol>
        <p>
            This approach ensures that all calculations are exact and avoids the pitfalls of floating-point inaccuracies.
            Alternatively, for more complex financial calculations, dedicated libraries (like `decimal.js` or `big.js`)
            can be used, which handle arbitrary-precision decimals.
        </p>
    </div>

    <script>
        // --- BROKEN CART (NAIVE FLOAT ARITHMETIC) ---
        let brokenCartItems = [];
        let brokenCartTotal = 0;

        function addItemToBrokenCart() {
            const nameInput = document.getElementById('brokenItemName');
            const priceInput = document.getElementById('brokenItemPrice');

            const name = nameInput.value;
            const price = parseFloat(priceInput.value);

            if (isNaN(price) || price <= 0) {
                alert('Please enter a valid price for the broken cart.');
                return;
            }

            brokenCartItems.push({ name, price });
            brokenCartTotal += price; // Direct float addition

            renderBrokenCart();
        }

        function renderBrokenCart() {
            const cartList = document.getElementById('brokenCartList');
            const totalDisplay = document.getElementById('brokenCartTotal');

            cartList.innerHTML = '';
            brokenCartItems.forEach(item => {
                const li = document.createElement('li');
                li.innerHTML = `<span>${item.name}</span><span>$${item.price.toFixed(2)}</span>`;
                cartList.appendChild(li);
            });

            // Note: toFixed(2) rounds the *display* but the underlying float value might still be off.
            totalDisplay.textContent = `Total: $${brokenCartTotal.toFixed(2)}`;
            document.getElementById('brokenComparisonResult').innerHTML = ''; // Clear previous comparison
        }

        function checkBrokenTotal() {
            const checkPriceInput = document.getElementById('brokenCheckPrice');
            const checkPrice = parseFloat(checkPriceInput.value);
            const resultDiv = document.getElementById('brokenComparisonResult');

            if (isNaN(checkPrice) || checkPrice <= 0) {
                resultDiv.className = 'warning';
                resultDiv.textContent = 'Please enter a valid price to check against.';
                return;
            }

            // THE FLAW: Direct comparison of floating-point numbers
            if (brokenCartTotal === checkPrice) {
                resultDiv.className = 'success';
                resultDiv.textContent = `SUCCESS! Total (${brokenCartTotal}) is EXACTLY ${checkPrice}`;
            } else {
                resultDiv.className = 'warning';
                resultDiv.textContent = `FAILURE! Total (${brokenCartTotal}) is NOT EXACTLY ${checkPrice}.
                                         (Actual internal value: ${brokenCartTotal}, Expected: ${checkPrice})`;
                console.log("Broken Cart Comparison Failure Details:");
                console.log(`brokenCartTotal: ${brokenCartTotal}`);
                console.log(`checkPrice: ${checkPrice}`);
                console.log(`brokenCartTotal === checkPrice: ${brokenCartTotal === checkPrice}`);
                console.log(`Difference: ${brokenCartTotal - checkPrice}`);
            }
        }


        // --- CORRECTED CART (PROPER DECIMAL HANDLING) ---
        let correctedCartItems = [];
        let correctedCartTotalCents = 0; // Store total in cents (integer)

        function addItemToCorrectedCart() {
            const nameInput = document.getElementById('correctedItemName');
            const priceInput = document.getElementById('correctedItemPrice');

            const name = nameInput.value;
            const priceString = priceInput.value;

            // Convert price string to cents as an integer
            // Example: "4.99" -> 499
            const priceCents = Math.round(parseFloat(priceString) * 100);

            if (isNaN(priceCents) || priceCents <= 0) {
                alert('Please enter a valid price for the corrected cart.');
                return;
            }

            correctedCartItems.push({ name, priceCents });
            correctedCartTotalCents += priceCents; // Exact integer addition

            renderCorrectedCart();
        }

        function renderCorrectedCart() {
            const cartList = document.getElementById('correctedCartList');
            const totalDisplay = document.getElementById('correctedCartTotal');

            cartList.innerHTML = '';
            correctedCartItems.forEach(item => {
                // Convert cents back to dollars for display
                const priceDollars = (item.priceCents / 100).toFixed(2);
                const li = document.createElement('li');
                li.innerHTML = `<span>${item.name}</span><span>$${priceDollars}</span>`;
                cartList.appendChild(li);
            });

            // Convert total cents back to dollars for display
            const totalDollars = (correctedCartTotalCents / 100).toFixed(2);
            totalDisplay.textContent = `Total: $${totalDollars}`;
            document.getElementById('correctedComparisonResult').innerHTML = ''; // Clear previous comparison
        }

        function checkCorrectedTotal() {
            const checkPriceInput = document.getElementById('correctedCheckPrice');
            const checkPriceString = checkPriceInput.value;
            const resultDiv = document.getElementById('correctedComparisonResult');

            // Convert check price to cents for comparison
            const checkPriceCents = Math.round(parseFloat(checkPriceString) * 100);

            if (isNaN(checkPriceCents) || checkPriceCents <= 0) {
                resultDiv.className = 'warning';
                resultDiv.textContent = 'Please enter a valid price to check against.';
                return;
            }

            // THE FIX: Compare integer cents
            if (correctedCartTotalCents === checkPriceCents) {
                resultDiv.className = 'success';
                resultDiv.textContent = `SUCCESS! Total ($${(correctedCartTotalCents/100).toFixed(2)}) is EXACTLY $${(checkPriceCents/100).toFixed(2)}`;
            } else {
                resultDiv.className = 'warning';
                resultDiv.textContent = `FAILURE! Total ($${(correctedCartTotalCents/100).toFixed(2)}) is NOT EXACTLY $${(checkPriceCents/100).toFixed(2)}`;
                console.log("Corrected Cart Comparison Failure Details (Should not happen if logic is correct):");
                console.log(`correctedCartTotalCents: ${correctedCartTotalCents}`);
                console.log(`checkPriceCents: ${checkPriceCents}`);
                console.log(`correctedCartTotalCents === checkPriceCents: ${correctedCartTotalCents === checkPriceCents}`);
            }
        }

        // Initial setup for demonstration
        window.onload = () => {
            // Pre-add some items to quickly demonstrate the issue
            document.getElementById('brokenItemName').value = "Item A";
            document.getElementById('brokenItemPrice').value = "4.99";
            addItemToBrokenCart();

            document.getElementById('brokenItemName').value = "Item B";
            document.getElementById('brokenItemPrice').value = "4.99";
            addItemToBrokenCart();

            document.getElementById('brokenItemName').value = "Item C";
            document.getElementById('brokenItemPrice').value = "4.99";
            addItemToBrokenCart();

            document.getElementById('correctedItemName').value = "Item X";
            document.getElementById('correctedItemPrice').value = "4.99";
            addItemToCorrectedCart();

            document.getElementById('correctedItemName').value = "Item Y";
            document.getElementById('correctedItemPrice').value = "4.99";
            addItemToCorrectedCart();

            document.getElementById('correctedItemName').value = "Item Z";
            document.getElementById('correctedItemPrice').value = "4.99";
            addItemToCorrectedCart();
        };
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### How to Use and Observe the Issue:

1.  **Save the code:** Save the entire block above as an `.html` file (e.g., `shopping_cart_demo.html`).
2.  **Open in browser:** Open the `shopping_cart_demo.html` file in any web browser.
3.  **Observe Initial State:**
    *   Both carts will start with three items of $4.99 each.
    *   The displayed total for both will be $14.97.
4.  **Test the "Broken Cart":**
    *   The "Check if total is:" input will be pre-filled with `14.97`.
    *   Click the "Check Total" button under the "Broken Cart" section.
    *   **Result:** You will see a `FAILURE!` message, indicating that `brokenCartTotal` is NOT EXACTLY `14.97`. Open your browser's developer console (F12) to see the `console.log` output, which will show the tiny difference causing the failure (e.g., `14.969999999999999` vs `14.97`).
5.  **Test the "Corrected Cart":**
    *   The "Check if total is:" input will also be pre-filled with `14.97`.
    *   Click the "Check Total" button under the "Corrected Cart" section.
    *   **Result:** You will see a `SUCCESS!` message, indicating the total is EXACTLY `14.97`.
6.  **Experiment:** Add more items with decimal prices (e.g., $0.10, $0.20) to the broken cart and try checking totals. The inaccuracies will become more pronounced or appear in different scenarios.

This example clearly demonstrates why relying on `===` for direct comparison of floating-point numbers, especially in financial contexts, is a dangerous practice.

