        <p>The core problem lies in how computers represent <span class="highlight">floating-point numbers</span> (like JavaScript's <code>Number</code> type, which is a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Double-precision_floating-point_format" target="_blank">double-precision 64-bit binary format</a>). Most decimal fractions (like 0.1, 0.01, 0.49, 0.99) cannot be represented exactly in binary floating-point. Just like 1/3 cannot be represented exactly as a finite decimal (0.333...), many decimal numbers cannot be represented exactly as a finite binary fraction.</p>

        <h3>The Consequences:</h3>
